  "prompt": "Who is Amartya Sen?",
  "response": "Amartya Sen is a renowned Indian economist and philosopher who has made significant contributions to welfare economics, social choice theory, economic and social justice, and the understanding of poverty and development. Born on November 3, 1933, in Santiniketan, India, he has taught at several prestigious institutions, including Harvard University, the London School of Economics, and the University of Cambridge.\n\nSen is particularly known for his work on the theory of social choice, which deals with aggregating individual preferences into collective decisions, and his development of the capability approach, which focuses on individuals' abilities to achieve well-being. His influential book \"Development as Freedom\" argues that development should be assessed by the extent to which people have the freedom to achieve valuable outcomes.\n\nHe was awarded the Nobel Memorial Prize in Economic Sciences in 1998 for his contributions to welfare economics. In addition to his academic work, Sen has actively engaged in public discourse on issues related to poverty, education, and health care, advocating for human rights and social justice.",
